n vielä molempien kuuleminen, joka antaa paljon tietoa monelle puoluekokousedustajalle. Täällä on puhuttu paljon molemmista ehdokkaista.'),(133193935,13386352,'Kokouspaikalla ehdokkaiden kannatuksesta liikkui monenlaista tietoa. Urpilaisen taustajoukoista arvioitiin, että molempien ehdokkaiden takana olisi nyt noin kaksisataa edustajaa. Näin ollen sata miettisi vielä valintaansa.'),(133193936,13386352,'Rinteen taustajoukoista kantautui ristiriitaista tietoa. Toisen arvion mukaan Rinne johtaisi niukasti, toisen mukaan hän olisi ollut parikymmentä ääntä Urpilaista jäljessä.'),(133193937,13386352,'Puoluekokous äänestää puheenjohtajasta perjantaiaamun aikana.'),(133193938,13386353,'Ilta-Sanomat kertoi eilen, että hämeenlinnalaismies voitti Pitkävedossa 1600 euroa viikonloppuna, kun hän veikkasi oikein Espanjan liigan ottelun lopputuloksen. Mies jäi kuitenkin ilman voittorahoja, koska hänelle kerrottiin maanantaina, että joku oli jo sunnuntai-iltana käynyt lunastamassa voiton.'),(133193939,13386353,'Veikkauksen sääntöjen mukaan voitot voi maksaa vain alkuperäistä kuponkia vastaan. Veikkauksen viestintä- ja vastuullisuusjohtaja Pekka Ilmivallan mukaan virheellisesti toiminut asiamies on voinut maksaa Pitkäveto-voiton huijarille ilman kuponkia pelkillä voittokupongin tiedoilla.'),(133193940,13386353,'− Voiton tiedot kun osaa päätteelle näppäillä, niin se on mahdollista, Ilmivalta kertoo.'),(133193941,13386353,'Ilmivalta kertoo, että alustavien tietojen mukaan näyttää siltä, että Veikkauksen asiamiestä olisi vedätetty.'),(133193942,13386353,'− Näyttäisi siltä, että hän on ainakin toiminut huolimattomasti. Missään tilanteessa ei pitäisi voittoja maksaa ilman virallista pelitodistetta, Ilmivalta sanoo.'),(133193943,13386353,'Vastaavankaltainen tapaus on sattunut kerran aikaisemmin, mutta siitä on jo aikaa muutama vuosi. Silloinkin voiton lunastukseen oli käytetty kupongin kopiota. Tuolloin kuva kupongista ei levinnyt niin kuin tässä tapauksessa Facebookin kautta.'),(133193944,13386353,'− Silloin ei vielä eletty näin aktiivista some-aikaa.'),(133193945,13386353,'Helsingin poliisi tutkii tapausta petoksena.'),(133193946,13386353,'Ilmivallan mukaan poliisitutkintaa tulee helpottamaan se, että Veikkauksella on hyvät seurantajärjestelmät, joista pystyy selvittämään, missä pelit on pelattu ja missä ja milloin voitot on lunastettu.'),(133193947,13386353,'Veikkauksesta kerrottiin aiemmin torstaina IS:lle, että voitto on nyt maksettu oikealle voittajalle.'),(133193948,13386354,'Spiritual exploration takes a lifetime—\"or some traditions would say lifetimes,\" says Michael Gayner, executive director of Shambhala Mountain Center in Red Feather Lakes, Colo. '),(133193949,13386354,'For those who can\'t spend years in deep contemplation, the Buddhist haven offers a low-commitment option—the one-day retreat. '),(133193950,13386354,'On the first Sunday of specified months, day trippers to Shambhala Mountain, a 600-acre Rocky Mountains property, can take part in meditation instruction, have lunch and tour the site\'s sacred monument, the Great Stupa of Dharmakaya. Then they can go home. '),(133193951,13386354,'It isn\'t one of the center\'s famous monthlong retreats. Still, Mr. Gayner says, \"there are a lot of people who just want to come somewhere that\'s really beautiful, decompress, hike around and maybe do some meditation.\" '),(133193952,13386354,'People are busy; budgets are tight: Spiritual-growth and yoga destinations are asking for shorter time commitments from their guests. '),(133193953,13386354,'Shorter stays attract new visitors and boost overall attendance, as some personal-growth centers that are known for programs lasting weeks have found. Many events start after work on Friday and end at noon Sunday. There are single-night stays, one-day programs and, at some urban and suburban oases, \"mini retreats\" of just a couple of hours. '),(133193954,13386354,'The Birchwood Center for Yoga and Massage in Nyack, N.Y., had been offering an annual weekend pilgrimage to Montauk, N.Y., for two years when it got the message from clients that Friday-through-Sunday was too much time away. Last year, owners                                                                        Charlene Bradin                                                                and                                                                        Betsy Ceva                                                                organized a \"stay-at-home vacation\" weekend of workshops in yoga, breathing and chakras. Even then, there were scheduling conflicts. \"People said they couldn\'t make Saturday, they couldn\'t make Sunday. So we said, \'Why are we shooting ourselves in the foot?\' \" Ms. Bradin says. '),(133193955,13386354,'The center decided to let attendees sign up for activities a la carte. The choose-your-own-adventure approach proved so popular that the center is offering its second such retreat next month. Saturday and Sunday activities begin at 11:30 a.m. and end in the early evening so participants can get home to children, spouses and pets. '),(133193956,13386354,'The abbreviated spiritual retreats include certain hallmarks that set them apart from a spa day or a resort getaway. Most include workshops or classes that encourage self-reflection. Some retreats are silent; others encourage talking and mingling. The goal in all cases is to provide attendees the chance to contemplate whatever needs contemplating. '),(133193957,13386354,'A weekend stay at Esalen, in Big Sur, Calif., costs as little as $405 for one person, including, at this rate, spartan accommodations, workshop tuition and meals. At Kripalu Center for Yoga & Health in the Massachusetts Berkshires, $876 buys a Friday-through-Sunday retreat in the center\'s swankiest single room—private bath, lake view—plus food and activities. Stay in a shared, dormitory-style room with a shared bath, and the weekend is $368.'),(133193958,13386354,'Rates get even smaller the longer one stays. At Omega Institute for Holistic Studies in Rhinebeck, N.Y., tuition for a July weekend workshop on \"Unleashing Boundless Abundance\" with spiritual leader Panache Desai is $375, or $120 a day. The six-day \"Awakening Your Soul Signature\" workshop that follows, also with Mr. Desai, is $595, or $99 a day. Room and board are extra.'),(133193959,13386354,'People who have been on short and long retreats say the latter lead to more-permanent results. \"The depth of the benefit is related to the length of time you step away,\" says Zara Watkins, a lawyer and yoga teacher in Brooklyn, N.Y., who recently made a six-week solo pilgrimage to India. \"The longer you can let go of all of those things you hold on to in life, like your job and relationships and toys and routines, the deeper into yourself you go,\" she says. But \"even an hour in a yoga class without your electronics is beneficial.\" '),(133193960,13386354,'Internet and cellphone service can be spotty at spiritual centers. At Omega, guests say there is decent phone reception in certain places on campus but the dining room doesn\'t seem to be one of them. \"That might be deliberate,\" says Saskia Shakin, a New York public-speaking coach who attends two or three short retreats there a year. '),(133193961,13386354,'The New York Insight Meditation Center, in New York City, hosts a monthly Day of Silence, led by Sandra Weinberg, a psychotherapist and co-founder of the center. The mini-retreat, from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m., attracts beginners and experienced meditators. Ms. Weinberg tries to encourage people to disconnect for the day. But during the lunch break, some participants head out to eat, phones in hand. \"We use so many things to avoid coming home to ourselves,\" she says. \"When we recognize that, things can start to slow down.\"'),(133193962,13386355,'Poliisilla on tällä hetkellä tieto viidestä epäilyttävästä tapauksesta, jotka ovat sattuneet Pirkkalassa, Vesilahdella ja Tampereella 29.4-6.5. Tapauksia